‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ffi/zig/                   # Zig FFI dispatcher (zero-cost C wrapper)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/docudactyl_ffi.zig # Multi-format parser (Poppler, Tesseract, FFmpeg, etc.)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ build.zig
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test/integration_test.zig
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ generated/abi/             # C headers generated from Idris2 ABI
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ deploy/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Containerfile          # Multi-stage build (Wolfi runtime)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ slurm-docudactyl.sh   # Slurm job script (64+ nodes)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .machine_readable/         # ALL structured metadata
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ .well-known/               # RFC 9116, ai.txt, humans.txt
```

## Core Invariants

1. **No state files in root** ‚Äî `.machine_readable/` is authoritative
2. **Chapel is the hot path** ‚Äî OCaml/Julia are NOT called during HPC runs
3. **Zig FFI has zero runtime overhead** ‚Äî compiles to same code as direct C calls
4. **No banned patterns in Idris2** ‚Äî no `believe_me`, `assert_total`, `unsafePerformIO`
5. **License: MPL-2.0** on all original code
6. **Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell** `<j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>`
7. **Containers use Podman** ‚Äî never Docker. Files named `Containerfile`, never `Dockerfile`
8. **Base images: Chainguard Wolfi** ‚Äî `cgr.dev/chainguard/wolfi-base:latest`

## Architecture (Hot Path)

```
Manifest (170M paths) ‚Üí Chapel (block-distribute across N locales)
  ‚Üí forall: Zig FFI (detect format, dispatch to C library)
    ‚Üí Poppler (PDF), Tesseract (Image OCR), FFmpeg (Audio/Video),
      libxml2 (EPUB), GDAL (GeoSpatial), libvips (Image metadata)
  ‚Üí Per-locale sharded output + checkpoint files
  ‚Üí Global reduce ‚Üí run-report.scm + run-report.json
```

## Session Startup

1. Read this manifest
2. Read `.machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml` for current progress
3. Read `.claude/CLAUDE.md` for code patterns
4. Check `TOPOLOGY.md` for completion dashboard

